He smelled of fishing bait and sunlight. <br><br>&quot;No-Fur. Longwalker. Why do you do this dance?&quot; <br><br>I sighed into the sand, the fishbone necklace bumping against my chin. Above, I felt the sky grow overcast, felt a coming rain over Kerra Isle. <br><br>&quot;I don't know, friend. To find a little peace.&quot;<br><br>I'd found peace there in Kerra, surprising myself as much as the catmen who took me in. Peace, and confusion. I had no idea how I came to be there. Only the vague recollection of the ghost-woman on the moon, teaching me the motions, the poses, in a fevered dream... and waking at the spires on Erud. I wandered in that dank forest for days and then... here. Among the Kerrans. Who looked at me with their strangely knowing eyes and still startled me with their quick, violent movements. <br><br>&quot;You know how I find peace?&quot; the catman muttered, leaning back onto his haunches. &quot;Fishing. There is peace in fishing. I like to dance, but there's no peace in it. But I dance faster than you.&quot; <br><br>&quot;I don't think this is a dance, Arlgrath.&quot; <br><br>&quot;What is it?&quot;<br><br>&quot;I... don't really know.&quot;<br><br>I stood up, brushed sand from my knees. The first kisses of rain began to pepper my face. My weapons of war were scattered all about -- the old man's sword, the whip that was a gift long ago from a giggling half-elven mystery of a woman, the ugly mining pick, the Northman's dagger I carried in honor of my father. I left them where they lay, my armor a lazy pile beside them, and waded out into the water. <br><br>&quot;I like it here, Arlgrath,&quot; I said, gliding onto my back. The water was cool, but pleasant. <br><br>&quot;But the Longwalker No-Fur will leave, of course,&quot; he growled. <br><br>&quot;It would be nice to stay. The world out there is ugly.&quot;<br><br>&quot;So stay. Fish with us. Go to war with us, against the large-heads and the dog-faces. Do your silly, slow dance.&quot; <br><br>I listened to the tigers growl in the distance, the Kerran kittens playing by the campfire. Gorillas hooted conversationally far away. I could hear an echo of silence. No voices shouted, in rough Human or bold Barbarian or spidery Elvish. <br><br>I waded until I stood only knee-deep in water. In the distance I could make out the greenish fog of the forest, the nightmarish trees. Beyond them, the spires. Beyond them, chaos and horror. And home. <br><br>&quot;I'm not ready to go back,&quot; I muttered absently. <br><br>&quot;Stay, Longwalker,&quot; the Kerran said, as if answering the most foolish question ever uttered. <br><br>I looked long and hard at my weapons. Instead I picked up a bone-handled knife and followed Arlgrath to the pier, where his brothers were preparing dinner. <br><br>&quot;For a while,&quot; I said, alone among friends.<br><br>/ooc Wrote this after hunting wharf rats and resting in Kerra alone for while. Criticism welcome -- tacky? Entertaining? <br><br>Lest<br>18th ranger <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=340.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=340.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.threadControl?topicID=340.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.subscribeUnregistered